<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880706-0137 </DOCNO><HL> United Technologies Unit Wins Army Job Totaling $54.1 Million </HL><SO> </SO><CO> UTX F MD HSI TXT </CO><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sikorsky Aircraft, a unit of United Technologies Corp., won a $54.1 million Army contract for production of UH-60 helicopters.    Ford Aerospace, a unit of Ford Motor Co., received contracts totaling $31.6 million for Sidewinder missile equipment for the Navy and Chaparral missile-engineering services for the Army.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. was given a $27.1 million Navy contract for production of land attack missiles.    Hi-Shear Technology Corp., a unit of Hi-Shear Industries Inc., received a $14.4 million Navy contract for electronic equipment.    Textron Inc. won a $12.3 million Air Force contract for bombs.    E. Walters andamp; Co. was issued an $11 million Army contract for 20mm cartridges. </TEXT></DOC>